headline: Home Depot Stock Beat Earnings and Raised Guidance. Why the Stock Fell.
summary: Home Depot  posted strong quarterly earnings and hiked the full-year outlook, but the stock was trending lower Tuesday morning after management hinted that the home-improvement recovery was still in progress.  Home-improvement demand has been under pressure for the better part of the past year or so.  The Federal Reserve’s move to cut interest rates will help reverse those trends, analysts say, an outlook that has given Home Depot stock a boost in the past couple of months.
